# Scenario 5: Filter and Search Collection  
# User Story: As a reader, I want to find books in my collection using filters and search

### 1. Filter books by reading status (currently reading)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/books/?reading_status=reading
Authorization: Token YOUR_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

### 2. Filter books by genre
GET http://localhost:8080/api/books/?genre=fantasy
Authorization: Token YOUR_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

### 3. Search books by title or author name
GET http://localhost:8080/api/books/?search=tolkien
Authorization: Token YOUR_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

### 4. Search books by title
GET http://localhost:8080/api/books/?search=hobbit
Authorization: Token YOUR_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

### 5. Get all reviews with rating filter
GET http://localhost:8080/api/reviews/?rating=5
Authorization: Token YOUR_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

### 6. Filter reviews by book
GET http://localhost:8080/api/reviews/?book=1
Authorization: Token YOUR_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

### 7. Browse all available books (not user-specific)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/browse/?search=fantasy
Authorization: Token YOUR_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

### 8. Get user's reading statistics
GET http://localhost:8080/api/books/stats/
Authorization: Token YOUR_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

### Expected Stats Response:
# {
#   "total_books": 2,
#   "want_to_read": 1,
#   "reading": 0,
#   "finished": 1,
#   "total_reviews": 1,
#   "average_rating": 5.0
# }

### 9. Get book recommendations (custom action)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/books/recommendations/
Authorization: Token YOUR_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json